label: %config
documentation: Defines a configuration section for setting options in an ODL file.

label: %define
documentation: Defines a section for specifying data model objects, parameters, functions, and entry points.

label: %populate
documentation: Defines a section for populating data model instances and setting parameter values.

label: action
documentation: Used to specify action callback handlers for objects or parameters.

label: add
documentation: Used in the %populate section to add instances to multi-instance objects.

label: as
documentation: Specifies an alias for imports or names synchronization templates.

label: call
documentation: Invokes a function for actions or event handlers.

label: counted
documentation: Used with 'with' to define an instance count parameter for multi-instance objects.

label: default
documentation: Sets a default value for a parameter in its definition.

label: entry-point
documentation: Defines an entry point function for initialization or cleanup.

label: event
documentation: Used with 'on' to define event callback handlers.

label: extend
documentation: Extends an object definition using a MIB.

label: false
documentation: Boolean value used in parameter values or configurations.

label: filter
documentation: Specifies a boolean expression to filter events in event handlers.

label: include
documentation: Includes another ODL file or directory for mandatory parsing.

label: #include
documentation: Includes another ODL file or directory optionally.

label: ?include
documentation: Conditionally includes one of two ODL files or directories.

label: &include
documentation: Includes an ODL file or directory for deferred (post) parsing.

label: import
documentation: Loads a shared object for function resolution.

label: instance
documentation: Used in %populate to specify an instance of a multi-instance object.

label: mib
documentation: Defines a Modular Information Block for extending objects.

label: object
documentation: Defines an ODL object in the data model.

label: on
documentation: Used to specify event or action handlers.

label: parameter
documentation: Defines a parameter within an object.

label: regexp
documentation: Specifies a regular expression for matching event names.

label: select
documentation: Selects an existing object to extend its definition.

label: using
documentation: Used with 'extend' to apply a MIB to an object.

label: true
documentation: Boolean value used in parameter values or configurations.

label: with
documentation: Used with 'counted' to define instance count parameters.

label: synchronize
documentation: Defines a synchronization context for data model objects or parameters.

label: RTLD_GLOBAL
documentation: Makes symbols in a shared object available for subsequent loads.

label: RTLD_NODELETE
documentation: Prevents unloading of a shared object after parsing.

label: RTLD_NOW
documentation: Resolves all symbols in a shared object before dlopen returns.

label: %batch
documentation: Optimizes synchronization of multiple parameters in a batch.

label: %global
documentation: Applies a configuration option globally across all scopes.

label: %in
documentation: Marks a function argument as input from caller to callee.

label: %instance
documentation: Makes a parameter or function usable on instance objects.

label: %key
documentation: Marks a parameter as a key for identifying instances.

label: %mandatory
documentation: Marks a function argument as required.

label: %out
documentation: Marks a function argument as output from callee to caller.

label: %persistent
documentation: Marks an object or parameter for persistent storage.

label: !persistent
documentation: Unsets the persistent attribute for an object or parameter.

label: %private
documentation: Makes an object, parameter, or function invisible to external sources.

label: !private
documentation: Unsets the private attribute for an object or parameter.

label: %protected
documentation: Marks an object, parameter, or function for internal use only.

label: !protected
documentation: Unsets the protected attribute for an object or parameter.

label: %read-only
documentation: Prevents external sources from modifying an object or parameter.

label: !read-only
documentation: Unsets the read-only attribute for an object or parameter.

label: %strict
documentation: Requires a function argument to match the defined type.

label: %template
documentation: Makes a parameter or function usable on template objects.

label: %unique
documentation: Ensures a parameter value is unique among instances.

label: %volatile
documentation: Marks a parameter as frequently changing, suppressing change events.

label: !volatile
documentation: Unsets the volatile attribute for a parameter.

label: %async
documentation: Marks a function as asynchronous, suitable for lengthy operations.

label: %write-once
documentation: Allows a parameter to be set only once.

label: bool
documentation: Boolean type for parameters or function arguments (true/false).

label: csv_string
documentation: Comma-separated string type for parameters or function arguments.

label: double
documentation: Double-precision floating-point type for function arguments.

label: datetime
documentation: String type for RFC-3339 formatted date-time values.

label: fd
documentation: File descriptor type for function arguments.

label: htable
documentation: Hash table type for function arguments.

label: int8
documentation: 8-bit signed integer type for parameters or function arguments.

label: int16
documentation: 16-bit signed integer type for parameters or function arguments.

label: int32
documentation: 32-bit signed integer type for parameters or function arguments.

label: int64
documentation: 64-bit signed integer type for parameters or function arguments.

label: list
documentation: List type for function arguments.

label: ssv_string
documentation: Space-separated string type for parameters or function arguments.

label: string
documentation: String type for parameters or function arguments.

label: uint8
documentation: 8-bit unsigned integer type for parameters or function arguments.

label: uint16
documentation: 16-bit unsigned integer type for parameters or function arguments.

label: uint32
documentation: 32-bit unsigned integer type for parameters or function arguments.

label: uint64
documentation: 64-bit unsigned integer type for parameters or function arguments.

label: variant
documentation: Variant type for function arguments, allowing multiple types.

label: void
documentation: Void type for function return values or arguments.

label: add-inst
documentation: Action for adding an instance to a multi-instance object.

label: del-inst
documentation: Action for deleting an instance from a multi-instance object.

label: describe
documentation: Action for describing an object or parameter.

label: list
documentation: Action for listing object contents.

label: read
documentation: Action for reading an object or parameter value.

label: validate
documentation: Action for validating an object or parameter.

label: write
documentation: Action for writing to an object or parameter.

label: translate
documentation: Action for translating values in synchronization blocks.

label: apply
documentation: Action for applying values in synchronization blocks.

Right-directional synchronization operator.
